Critical
Hardcoded secrets — docker-compose.yml has DB password postgres and JWT secret "replace_with_your_production_secret" in plain text. No .env or .env.example exists.

Zero test infrastructure — No test files, no test framework installed (no jest/vitest/playwright), both root and backend have placeholder "test": "echo Error".

Hardcoded API URL — http://localhost:2000 is hardcoded in lib/api.ts and store/authSlice.ts. Won't work outside local dev.

Medium

No refresh token rotation — Old refresh tokens stay valid after use.
Missing DB indexes — FK columns like Message.sender_id, Tournament.status, Match.tournament_id, etc. are un-indexed.
Missing cascade rules — Deleting a User who created teams or is a tournament participant will fail with FK violations.

Race condition on token refresh — Multiple concurrent 401s each independently call refreshAccessToken().
req.user typed as always-present — express.d.ts doesn't mark user as optional, masking runtime null access on unauthenticated routes.
No real build step — tsx runs TypeScript at runtime in production Docker; no compiled JS output, no multi-stage build.
 Actively served at /api-docs but provides no value.
Low 
No generic API error handling — Every frontend caller must individually parse errors from apiFetch.
useRequireAuth doesn't check token expiry — User sees protected page briefly before first 401 kicks them out.
Dockerfile double-copies prisma/ — Minor image build inefficiency.

